title: Cereza Barber and Cal Trans District 4 Communications (Marin County Dept. of Health and Human Services)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All communications between Cereza Barbar, who is County of Marin Health and Human Service Senior Project Coordinator. The following are the individual requests:

All written and electronic communications between Cereza Barber and Cheryl Chambers between January 1st, 2021 to October 14th 2023

All written and electronic communications between Cereza Barber and Debra Nelson between January 1st, 2021 to October 14th 2023

All written and electronic communications between Cereza Barber and Jacelyn Sharabati between January 1st, 2021 to October 14th 2023

All written and electronic communications between Cereza Barber and Briana Dixon between January 1st, 2021 to October 14th 2023

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robbie Powelson

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Records, Thomas Francis Gambino
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

All records of border crossing and/or secondary screening or other interactions with CBP for the individual named Thomas Francis Gambino, who had the date of birth of August 23, 1929.

Attached, find a newspaper article proving Thomas Gambino is dead. Records concerning Gambino as the main subject have diminished privacy interest under both FOIA and the Privacy Act and are disclosable.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

T. McElwee
